---
import ToolPage from '../layouts/ToolPage.astro';
---
<ToolPage
  title="Cron Generator &amp; Explainer, build and read crontab expressions | KB Cafe"
  description="Build a crontab schedule with simple controls and read any cron expression in plain English. Free, fast, client-side. See the next run times instantly."
  path="/cron-generator"
  eyebrow="Time &amp; Cron · Scheduling"
  h1="Cron Generator"
  tagline="Build a schedule with simple controls, or paste a cron expression to read it in plain English, with the next run times. Runs entirely in your browser."
>
  <div class="pane" style="margin-bottom:14px">
    <div class="pane-label"><span>Cron expression</span><span id="valid-flag" class="vflag"></span></div>
    <input id="expr" class="ta cron-input" style="min-height:auto;height:auto" spellcheck="false" value="0 9 * * 1-5" />
  </div>

  <p class="english" id="english"></p>

  <div class="presets row" id="presets">
    <button class="chip" data-e="* * * * *">every minute</button>
    <button class="chip" data-e="*/5 * * * *">every 5 min</button>
    <button class="chip" data-e="0 * * * *">hourly</button>
    <button class="chip" data-e="0 0 * * *">daily midnight</button>
    <button class="chip" data-e="0 9 * * 1-5">weekdays 9am</button>
    <button class="chip" data-e="0 0 * * 0">weekly (Sun)</button>
    <button class="chip" data-e="0 0 1 * *">monthly</button>
    <button class="chip" data-e="0 0 1 1 *">yearly</button>
  </div>

  <div class="builder" id="builder">
    <div class="field"><label>Minute</label><input data-i="0" value="0" /><span class="hint">0–59</span></div>
    <div class="field"><label>Hour</label><input data-i="1" value="9" /><span class="hint">0–23</span></div>
    <div class="field"><label>Day of month</label><input data-i="2" value="*" /><span class="hint">1–31</span></div>
    <div class="field"><label>Month</label><input data-i="3" value="*" /><span class="hint">1–12</span></div>
    <div class="field"><label>Day of week</label><input data-i="4" value="1-5" /><span class="hint">0–6 (Sun=0)</span></div>
  </div>

  <div class="nextruns" id="nextruns"></div>

  <Fragment slot="explainer">
    <h2>The five cron fields</h2>
    <p>A standard cron expression is five fields separated by spaces, each controlling one unit of time:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>minute</code> (0–59)</li>
      <li><code>hour</code> (0–23)</li>
      <li><code>day of month</code> (1–31)</li>
      <li><code>month</code> (1–12)</li>
      <li><code>day of week</code> (0–6, where 0 and 7 are both Sunday)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Read together, <code>0 9 * * 1-5</code> means &ldquo;at 09:00, Monday through Friday.&rdquo;</p>

    <h3>The operators</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><code>*</code>: every value (&ldquo;every minute&rdquo;, &ldquo;every day&rdquo;).</li>
      <li><code>,</code>: a list, e.g. <code>1,15,30</code>.</li>
      <li><code>-</code>: a range, e.g. <code>1-5</code> (Mon–Fri).</li>
      <li><code>/</code>: a step, e.g. <code>*/15</code> (every 15 units) or <code>0-30/10</code>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>A subtle gotcha: day-of-month vs day-of-week</h3>
    <p>
      When <em>both</em> day-of-month and day-of-week are restricted (neither is <code>*</code>),
      classic cron runs the job when <strong>either</strong> matches, an OR, not an AND. So
      <code>0 0 13 * 5</code> fires on the 13th <em>and</em> every Friday, not just Friday the 13th.
      Keep one field as <code>*</code> to avoid surprises.
    </p>

    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <details class="faq"><summary>Is this standard cron or the 6-field variant?</summary>
      <p>This tool uses the classic 5-field crontab format used by Linux cron, most CI schedulers, and Vercel Cron. Some systems (Quartz, some Kubernetes setups) add a seconds field for 6 fields.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq"><summary>What timezone do the next run times use?</summary>
      <p>The preview next-run times are computed in <em>your</em> local timezone for readability. Real cron runs in the server&rsquo;s timezone, check your platform&rsquo;s docs (many CI systems default to UTC).</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq"><summary>Does anything get uploaded?</summary>
      <p>No. Parsing and the next-run preview are computed in your browser, so it works offline.</p>
    </details>

    <h3>Related references</h3>
    <p>Scheduling a job that emits JSON? Type it with <a href="/json-to-typescript">JSON → TypeScript</a>. Refreshing auth on a schedule? Inspect tokens with the <a href="/jwt-decoder">JWT decoder</a>.</p>
  </Fragment>
</ToolPage>

<style is:global> /* JS-created elements need unscoped CSS, see context-budget-analyzer */
  .cron-input{font-size:22px !important;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.04em;padding:14px 16px !important;text-align:left}
  .vflag{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;font-weight:700}
  .vflag.ok{color:#2f7d32} .vflag.bad{color:var(--coral-deep)}
  .english{font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:700;font-size:clamp(20px,3vw,28px);line-height:1.25;
    color:var(--ink);margin:16px 0 6px;min-height:1.2em}
  .english b{color:var(--coral)}
  .presets{margin:14px 0 4px}
  .builder{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr);gap:12px;margin:22px 0 6px}
  .field{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px}
  .field label{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-soft)}
  .field input{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:16px;font-weight:700;text-align:center;border:1.5px solid var(--ink);
    border-radius:11px;background:var(--cream);color:var(--ink);padding:11px 6px;outline:0;width:100%}
  .field input:focus{box-shadow:5px 5px 0 var(--coral)}
  .field input.bad{border-color:var(--coral-deep);color:var(--coral-deep)}
  .field .hint{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:10.5px;color:var(--ink-soft);opacity:.7;text-align:center}
  .nextruns{margin-top:22px;font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:13px;color:var(--ink-soft)}
  .nextruns h3{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:9px}
  .nextruns ol{list-style:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px}
  .nextruns li{padding:8px 12px;background:var(--cream);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:9px}
  @media(max-width:620px){.builder{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}}
</style>

<script is:inline>
  const $ = id => document.getElementById(id);
  const exprEl = $('expr'), englishEl = $('english'), flagEl = $('valid-flag'),
        nextEl = $('nextruns'), builderInputs = [...document.querySelectorAll('#builder input')];
  const DOW = ['Sunday','Monday','Tuesday','Wednesday','Thursday','Friday','Saturday'];
  const MON = ['','January','February','March','April','May','June','July','August','September','October','November','December'];
  const RANGES = [[0,59],[0,23],[1,31],[1,12],[0,7]];

  // Parse one field into a sorted set of allowed integers; throw on invalid.
  function parseField(field, idx){
    const [lo, hi] = RANGES[idx];
    const out = new Set();
    for(const part of field.split(',')){
      let m;
      if(part === '*'){ for(let i=lo;i<=hi;i++) out.add(i); continue; }
      if((m = part.match(/^\*\/(\d+)$/))){
        const step = +m[1]; if(step<1) throw 0;
        for(let i=lo;i<=hi;i+=step) out.add(i); continue;
      }
      if((m = part.match(/^(\d+)-(\d+)\/(\d+)$/))){
        const a=+m[1], b=+m[2], step=+m[3]; if(step<1||a>b||a<lo||b>hi) throw 0;
        for(let i=a;i<=b;i+=step) out.add(i); continue;
      }
      if((m = part.match(/^(\d+)-(\d+)$/))){
        const a=+m[1], b=+m[2]; if(a>b||a<lo||b>hi) throw 0;
        for(let i=a;i<=b;i++) out.add(i); continue;
      }
      if((m = part.match(/^(\d+)$/))){
        const v=+m[1]; if(v<lo||v>hi) throw 0; out.add(v); continue;
      }
      throw 0;
    }
    // normalize Sunday 7 -> 0 for day-of-week
    if(idx === 4 && out.has(7)){ out.add(0); out.delete(7); }
    return out;
  }

  function describeField(field, idx, names){
    if(field === '*') return null;
    let m;
    if((m = field.match(/^\*\/(\d+)$/))) return `every ${ordinalStep(+m[1])}`;
    const parts = field.split(',').map(p => {
      let mm;
      if((mm = p.match(/^(\d+)-(\d+)$/))) return names ? `${names[+mm[1]]} through ${names[+mm[2]]}` : `${mm[1]}–${mm[2]}`;
      if((mm = p.match(/^(\d+)$/))) return names ? names[+mm[1]] : mm[1];
      return p;
    });
    return joinList(parts);
  }
  function ordinalStep(n){ return n === 1 ? 'unit' : n + (n===2?'nd':n===3?'rd':'th'); }
  function joinList(a){ return a.length <= 1 ? a[0] : a.slice(0,-1).join(', ') + ' and ' + a[a.length-1]; }
  function pad(n){ return String(n).padStart(2,'0'); }

  function toEnglish(fields){
    const [min, hr, dom, mon, dow] = fields;
    let timePart;
    // exact time vs minute patterns
    if(/^\d+$/.test(min) && /^\d+$/.test(hr)) timePart = `at <b>${pad(+hr)}:${pad(+min)}</b>`;
    else if(min === '*' && hr === '*') timePart = 'every minute';
    else {
      const mm = min === '*' ? 'every minute' : (min.match(/^\*\/(\d+)$/) ? `every ${min.match(/^\*\/(\d+)$/)[1]} minutes` : `at minute ${describeField(min,0)||min}`);
      const hh = hr === '*' ? '' : ` past hour ${describeField(hr,1)||hr}`;
      timePart = mm + hh;
    }
    const monStr = describeField(mon, 3, MON);
    const domStr = describeField(dom, 2);
    const dowStr = describeField(dow, 4, DOW);

    let dayPart = '';
    if(domStr && dowStr) dayPart = ` on day-of-month ${domStr} <b>and</b> on ${dowStr}`;
    else if(domStr) dayPart = ` on the ${domStr}${/^\d+$/.test(dom)?'th':''} of the month`;
    else if(dowStr) dayPart = ` on <b>${dowStr}</b>`;
    const monPart = monStr ? ` in ${monStr}` : '';
    return `Runs ${timePart}${dayPart}${monPart}.`;
  }

  // compute next N run times in local tz by brute-force minute scan
  function nextRuns(sets, n){
    const res = [];
    const d = new Date(); d.setSeconds(0,0); d.setMinutes(d.getMinutes()+1);
    const [mins, hrs, doms, mons, dows] = sets;
    const domRestricted = doms.size < 31, dowRestricted = dows.size < 7;
    let guard = 0;
    while(res.length < n && guard++ < 366*24*60){
      const dayOk = (domRestricted && dowRestricted)
        ? (doms.has(d.getDate()) || dows.has(d.getDay()))
        : (doms.has(d.getDate()) && dows.has(d.getDay()));
      if(mins.has(d.getMinutes()) && hrs.has(d.getHours()) && mons.has(d.getMonth()+1) && dayOk){
        res.push(new Date(d));
      }
      d.setMinutes(d.getMinutes()+1);
    }
    return res;
  }

  function run(){
    const fields = exprEl.value.trim().split(/\s+/);
    builderInputs.forEach(inp => inp.classList.remove('bad'));
    if(fields.length !== 5){
      flagEl.className = 'vflag bad'; flagEl.textContent = '✕ need 5 fields';
      englishEl.innerHTML = `<span style="color:var(--coral-deep)">A cron expression needs exactly 5 fields.</span>`;
      nextEl.innerHTML = ''; return;
    }
    let sets;
    try { sets = fields.map((f,i) => parseField(f,i)); }
    catch {
      flagEl.className = 'vflag bad'; flagEl.textContent = '✕ invalid';
      englishEl.innerHTML = `<span style="color:var(--coral-deep)">One or more fields are out of range or malformed.</span>`;
      nextEl.innerHTML = ''; return;
    }
    flagEl.className = 'vflag ok'; flagEl.textContent = '✓ valid';
    englishEl.innerHTML = toEnglish(fields);
    // sync builder inputs
    builderInputs.forEach(inp => { inp.value = fields[+inp.dataset.i]; });
    // next runs
    const runs = nextRuns(sets, 5);
    nextEl.innerHTML = `<h3>Next ${runs.length} runs (your local time)</h3><ol>` +
      runs.map(r => `<li>${r.toLocaleString(undefined,{weekday:'short',year:'numeric',month:'short',day:'numeric',hour:'2-digit',minute:'2-digit'})}</li>`).join('') +
      `</ol>`;
  }

  function fromBuilder(){
    exprEl.value = builderInputs.map(i => i.value.trim() || '*').join(' ');
    run();
  }

  exprEl.addEventListener('input', run);
  builderInputs.forEach(inp => inp.addEventListener('input', fromBuilder));
  $('presets').addEventListener('click', e => {
    const b = e.target.closest('.chip'); if(!b) return;
    exprEl.value = b.dataset.e; run();
  });
  run();
</script>
